headline: AP sources: Asylum limits at border expected to end May 23
author: COLLEEN LONG
sentences: WASHINGTON (AP) — The Biden administration is expected to end the asylum limits at the U.S.-Mexico border by May 23 that were put in place to prevent the spread of COVID-19, according to people familiar with the matter.
